h and success, but many organisations need help to hire the right leaders. In this blog post, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);">Dr Richard Dune</span></i></a> will discuss insights from an insightful Harvard Business Review article by Josh Bersin and Tomas Chamoro-Premuzic titled "Hire leaders for what they can do, not what they have done".<br><br>Dr Dune will also share personal examples from health and social care and the tech industry. Finally, he will make recommendations for organisations on how to build strong and effective leadership teams.
